-- Tottenham Blocks Blackburn Move for Sherwood: Soccer Roundup
-- B y   A l e x   D u f f
-- 2012-10-01T09:07:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-01/tottenham-blocks-blackburn-move-for-sherwood-soccer-roundup.html
The following is a roundup of soccer
stories from U.K. newspapers, with clickable Internet links.  Sherwood Move  Tottenham rejected an approach by Blackburn to hire Tim Sherwood as coach, the  Daily Mail  reported.  Sherwood, who trains young players at Spurs, doesn’t have
any ambition to become a head coach, the Mail said. Sherwood was
captain when Rovers won the 1995 Premiership title.  Shearer Return  Alan Shearer  is interested in coaching former club
Blackburn, the  Daily Mirror  reported.  Barnsley manager Keith Hill is also a candidate for the
job, the  Daily Telegraph  reported.  Real to Royal  Reading may sign Russian winger Denis Cheryshev from Real
Madrid’s B team, the  Daily Mirror  reported.  Royals part-owner Anton Zingarevich said the move is
possible after watching the 21-year-old play against Barcelona’s
second team, the Mirror said.  Aguero Lament  Manchester City striker  Sergio Aguero  says Premier League
referees are biased against foreign players, the  Daily Telegraph 
reported.  Aguero was speaking after City beat Fulham 2-1 to avoid a
run of five straight games without a win.  To contact the reporters on this story:
